istener: (context, state) {},\n\n\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0),\n\n\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0BlocListe
ner<BlocC, BlocCState>(\n\n\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0listener: (context, state) {}
,\n\n\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0),\n\n\\],\n\nchild: ChildA(),\n\n)\n\n### BlocConsumer\n\n
BlocConsumer exposes a builder\xa0and listener\xa0in order react to new states. 
BlocConsumer\xa0is analogous to a nested BlocListener\xa0and BlocBuilder\xa0but 
reduces the amount of boilerplate needed. BlocConsumer\xa0should only be used wh
en it is necessary to both rebuild UI and execute other reactions to state chang
es in the bloc. BlocConsumer\xa0takes a required BlocWidgetBuilder\xa0and BlocWi
dgetListener\xa0and an optional bloc, BlocBuilderCondition, and BlocListenerCond
ition.\n\nIf the bloc\xa0parameter is omitted, BlocConsumer\xa0will automaticall
y perform a lookup using BlocProvider\xa0and the current BuildContext.\n\nBlocCo
nsumer<BlocA, BlocAState>(\n\nlistener: (context, state) {\n\n\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0//
do stuff here based on BlocA\'s state\n\n},\n\nbuilder: (context, state) {\n\n\x
a0\xa0\xa0\xa0// return widget here based on BlocA\'s state\n\n}\n\n)\n\nAn opti
onal listenWhen\xa0and buildWhen\xa0can be implemented for more granular control
over when the listener and builder\xa0are called. The listenWhen\xa0and buildWhe
n\xa0will be invoked on each bloc\xa0state\xa0change. They each take the previou
s state\xa0and current state\xa0and must return a bool\xa0which determines wheth
er or not the builder\xa0and/or listener\xa0function will be invoked. The previo
us state\xa0will be initialized to the state\xa0of the bloc\xa0when the BlocCons
umer\xa0is initialized. listenWhen\xa0and buildWhen\xa0are optional and if they 
aren\'t implemented, they will default to true.\n\nBlocConsumer<BlocA, BlocAStat
e>(\n\nlistenWhen: (previous, current) {\n\n\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0// return true/false
to determine whether or not\n\n\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0// to invoke listener with state\
n\n},\n\nlistener: (context, state) {\n\n\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0// do stuff here based 
on BlocA\'s state\n\n},\n\nbuildWhen: (previous, current) {\n\n\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0/
/ return true/false to determine whether or not\n\n\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0// to rebuild
the widget with state\n\n},\n\nbuilder: (context, state) {\n\n\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0//
return widget here based on BlocA\'s state\n\n}\n\n)\n\n---\n\nTitle: Flutter Bl
ocConsumer react only to certain state property changes\nDate: 2023-11-25\nURL: 
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/77545196/flutter-blocconsumer-react-only-to-
certain-state-property-changes\nSummary: We use build when to tell the bloc cons
umer/builder that we it needs to rebuild the widget based on specific things cha
nged between previous and current state.Read more\n\nThere are two approaches to
achieve this.\n\n### 1\\. Bloc consumer with buildWhen\n\nWe use build when to t
ell the bloc consumer/builder that we it needs to rebuild the widget based on sp
ecific things changed between `previous` and `current` state.\n\nex.:\n\n```\nBl
ocBuilder<TestBloc, TestState>(\n  builder: (context, state) {\n    return Text(
\n      \'${state.a + state.b + state.c + state.d}\',\n    );\n  },\n  buildWhen
: (previous, current) {\n    return previous.a != current.a ||\n        previous
.b != current.b ||\n        previous.c != current.c;\n  },\n),\n\n```\n\nin this
example widget will only be built again when a, b, or c change.\n\n### 2\\. Bloc
Selector\n\nBlocSelector is the widget used for listening and consuming specific
parts of the bloc. So when we need to use only 3 parameters of the state we can 
have this example:\n\n```\nBlocSelector<TestBloc, TestState, int>(\n  selector: 
(state) {\n    return state.a + state.b + state.c;\n  },\n  builder: (context, a
bcState) {\n    return Text(\'Updated value is: $abcState\');\n  },\n),\n\n```\n
\nThese two different approaches have different use cases.\n\nThe **1st** approa
ch (build when) is used when you want the whole state in the builder function an
d your widget, but you want the widget to rebuild only when certain parts of the
state is changed.\n\nThe **2nd** approach (bloc selector) is used when you want 
to use specific parameters of the bloc for a widget render, and also this widget
should not be built again if other parts of bloc get updated.\n\n---\n\nTitle: B
